cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about crowd counting, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a learning method that involves training a model with weak supervision, which falls under the scope of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of auxiliary tasks to improve the performance of the model, which is related to multi-task learning. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new approach, which is related to the evaluation of algorithms. Hence, cs.CR (Computing Research Repository) is also a possible sub-category.
